HEADWORD: Intelligencer
<hw>In*tel"li*gen*cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or
that which, sends or conveys intelligence or news; a
messenger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the intriguers in foreign politics, all the spies, and all the
<qex>intelligencers</qex> . . . acted solely upon that principle.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intelligencing</ent>⟦br⟧
